has been dreaming about making since the 80's. My Uncle still has a prototype my Dad made a a teen in his shop.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/njvM8lj.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>My parents are getting divorced after a long few years of mental illness and huge life changes and working on this project together has not only brought us together but also made him happier than I have seen in 15 years or so.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/7b5eflg.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>He has absolutely no doubt that I can "sell them on the internet". I love that he has faith in me and I really do believe in his product but I have no idea where to start.

